COST VS TGT

In[2]:
# Import required libraries
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
from google.colab import files
import statsmodels.api as sm
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller, kpss
from statsmodels.tsa.arima.model import ARIMA
from statsmodels.tsa.vector_ar.vecm import coint_johansen
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Upload Excel files
print("Please upload COST Excel file")
cost_upload = files.upload()
cost_filename = list(cost_upload.keys())[0]
cost_df = pd.read_excel(cost_filename)

print("Please upload TGT Excel file")
tgt_upload = files.upload()
tgt_filename = list(tgt_upload.keys())[0]
tgt_df = pd.read_excel(tgt_filename)

# Print available columns with better formatting
print("\nCOST DataFrame columns:")
for col in cost_df.columns:
    print(f"- '{col}'")
print("\nTGT DataFrame columns:")
for col in tgt_df.columns:
    print(f"- '{col}'")

# Ask user for the correct column name with guidance
print("\nNote: Enter the exact column name from above, including any spaces or case sensitivity")
close_column = input("Please enter the column name containing closing prices: ").strip()

# Verify the column exists in both DataFrames
if close_column not in cost_df.columns or close_column not in tgt_df.columns:
    print(f"Error: Column '{close_column}' not found in one or both DataFrames")
    print("Available columns in COST:", list(cost_df.columns))
    print("Available columns in TGT:", list(tgt_df.columns))
    raise KeyError(f"Column '{close_column}' not found")

# Extract closing prices and clean the data
try:
    cost_close = cost_df[close_column].dropna()  # Remove NaN values
    tgt_close = tgt_df[close_column].dropna()  # Remove NaN values
except KeyError as e:
    print(f"Unexpected error accessing column '{close_column}': {e}")
    raise

# Check for infinite values and remove them
cost_close = cost_close[np.isfinite(cost_close)]
tgt_close = tgt_close[np.isfinite(tgt_close)]

# Ensure both series have the same length
min_length = min(len(cost_close), len(tgt_close))
cost_close = cost_close[:min_length]
tgt_close = tgt_close[:min_length]

# Check if data is empty after cleaning
if len(cost_close) == 0 or len(tgt_close) == 0:
    raise ValueError("One or both series are empty after removing NaNs and infinite values. Please check your data.")

# Function for unit root tests
def unit_root_tests(series, name):
    print(f"\nUnit Root Tests for {name}:")

    # ADF Test
    adf_result = adfuller(series)
    print("ADF Test:")
    print(f'ADF Statistic: {adf_result[0]:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {adf_result[1]:.4f}')
    print(f'Critical Values: {adf_result[4]}')

    # KPSS Test
    kpss_result = kpss(series)
    print("\nKPSS Test:")
    print(f'KPSS Statistic: {kpss_result[0]:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {kpss_result[1]:.4f}')
    print(f'Critical Values: {kpss_result[3]}')

# Perform unit root tests
unit_root_tests(cost_close, "COST")
unit_root_tests(tgt_close, "TGT")

# Difference the series if non-stationary
cost_diff = cost_close.diff().dropna()
tgt_diff = tgt_close.diff().dropna()

# Function to find best ARMA model (using ARIMA with d=0)
def find_best_arma(series, name, max_p=3, max_q=3):
    best_aic = float('inf')
    best_order = None

    for p in range(max_p + 1):
        for q in range(max_q + 1):
            try:
                model = ARIMA(series, order=(p, 0, q))
                results = model.fit()
                if results.aic < best_aic:
                    best_aic = results.aic
                    best_order = (p, 0, q)
            except:
                continue

    print(f"\nBest ARMA model for {name}:")
    print(f"Order: {best_order}")
    print(f"AIC: {best_aic:.2f}")

    best_model = ARIMA(series, order=best_order).fit()
    return best_model

# Fit ARMA models
cost_arma = find_best_arma(cost_diff, "COST")
tgt_arma = find_best_arma(tgt_diff, "TGT")

# Cointegration test
def cointegration_test(df):
    result = coint_johansen(df, det_order=0, k_ar_diff=1)
    print("\nJohansen Cointegration Test:")
    print(f"Trace statistic: {result.lr1}")
    print(f"Critical values (90%, 95%, 99%): {result.cvt}")

    for i in range(len(result.lr1)):
        if result.lr1[i] > result.cvt[i, 1]:  # 95% critical value
            print(f"r = {i}: Cointegration exists at 95% confidence level")
        else:
            print(f"r = {i}: No cointegration at 95% confidence level")

# Prepare data for cointegration
coint_df = pd.DataFrame({
    'COST': cost_close,
    'TGT': tgt_close
}).dropna()

# Run cointegration test
cointegration_test(coint_df)

# Plot the series
plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
plt.plot(cost_close, label='COST')
plt.plot(tgt_close, label='TGT')
plt.title('COST vs TGT Closing Prices')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

# Plot the differenced series
plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
plt.plot(cost_diff, label='COST Diff')
plt.plot(tgt_diff, label='TGT Diff')
plt.title('Differenced Series')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

COST VS INTC

In[3]:
# Import required libraries
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
from google.colab import files
import statsmodels.api as sm
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller, kpss
from statsmodels.tsa.arima.model import ARIMA
from statsmodels.tsa.vector_ar.vecm import coint_johansen
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Upload Excel files
print("Please upload COST Excel file")
cost_upload = files.upload()
cost_filename = list(cost_upload.keys())[0]
cost_df = pd.read_excel(cost_filename)

print("Please upload INTC Excel file")
intc_upload = files.upload()
intc_filename = list(intc_upload.keys())[0]
intc_df = pd.read_excel(intc_filename)

# Print available columns with better formatting
print("\nCOST DataFrame columns:")
for col in cost_df.columns:
    print(f"- '{col}'")
print("\nINTC DataFrame columns:")
for col in intc_df.columns:
    print(f"- '{col}'")

# Ask user for the correct column name with guidance
print("\nNote: Enter the exact column name from above, including any spaces or case sensitivity")
close_column = input("Please enter the column name containing closing prices: ").strip()

# Verify the column exists in both DataFrames
if close_column not in cost_df.columns or close_column not in intc_df.columns:
    print(f"Error: Column '{close_column}' not found in one or both DataFrames")
    print("Available columns in COST:", list(cost_df.columns))
    print("Available columns in INTC:", list(intc_df.columns))
    raise KeyError(f"Column '{close_column}' not found")

# Extract closing prices and clean the data
try:
    cost_close = cost_df[close_column].dropna()  # Remove NaN values
    intc_close = intc_df[close_column].dropna()  # Remove NaN values
except KeyError as e:
    print(f"Unexpected error accessing column '{close_column}': {e}")
    raise

# Check for infinite values and remove them
cost_close = cost_close[np.isfinite(cost_close)]
intc_close = intc_close[np.isfinite(intc_close)]

# Ensure both series have the same length
min_length = min(len(cost_close), len(intc_close))
cost_close = cost_close[:min_length]
intc_close = intc_close[:min_length]

# Check if data is empty after cleaning
if len(cost_close) == 0 or len(intc_close) == 0:
    raise ValueError("One or both series are empty after removing NaNs and infinite values. Please check your data.")

# Function for unit root tests
def unit_root_tests(series, name):
    print(f"\nUnit Root Tests for {name}:")

    # ADF Test
    adf_result = adfuller(series)
    print("ADF Test:")
    print(f'ADF Statistic: {adf_result[0]:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {adf_result[1]:.4f}')
    print(f'Critical Values: {adf_result[4]}')

    # KPSS Test
    kpss_result = kpss(series)
    print("\nKPSS Test:")
    print(f'KPSS Statistic: {kpss_result[0]:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {kpss_result[1]:.4f}')
    print(f'Critical Values: {kpss_result[3]}')

# Perform unit root tests
unit_root_tests(cost_close, "COST")
unit_root_tests(intc_close, "INTC")

# Difference the series if non-stationary
cost_diff = cost_close.diff().dropna()
intc_diff = intc_close.diff().dropna()

# Function to find best ARMA model (using ARIMA with d=0)
def find_best_arma(series, name, max_p=3, max_q=3):
    best_aic = float('inf')
    best_order = None

    for p in range(max_p + 1):
        for q in range(max_q + 1):
            try:
                model = ARIMA(series, order=(p, 0, q))
                results = model.fit()
                if results.aic < best_aic:
                    best_aic = results.aic
                    best_order = (p, 0, q)
            except:
                continue

    print(f"\nBest ARMA model for {name}:")
    print(f"Order: {best_order}")
    print(f"AIC: {best_aic:.2f}")

    best_model = ARIMA(series, order=best_order).fit()
    return best_model

# Fit ARMA models
cost_arma = find_best_arma(cost_diff, "COST")
intc_arma = find_best_arma(intc_diff, "INTC")

# Cointegration test
def cointegration_test(df):
    result = coint_johansen(df, det_order=0, k_ar_diff=1)
    print("\nJohansen Cointegration Test:")
    print(f"Trace statistic: {result.lr1}")
    print(f"Critical values (90%, 95%, 99%): {result.cvt}")

    for i in range(len(result.lr1)):
        if result.lr1[i] > result.cvt[i, 1]:  # 95% critical value
            print(f"r = {i}: Cointegration exists at 95% confidence level")
        else:
            print(f"r = {i}: No cointegration at 95% confidence level")

# Prepare data for cointegration
coint_df = pd.DataFrame({
    'COST': cost_close,
    'INTC': intc_close
}).dropna()

# Run cointegration test
cointegration_test(coint_df)

# Plot the series
plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
plt.plot(cost_close, label='COST')
plt.plot(intc_close, label='INTC')
plt.title('COST vs INTC Closing Prices')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

# Plot the differenced series
plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
plt.plot(cost_diff, label='COST Diff')
plt.plot(intc_diff, label='INTC Diff')
plt.title('Differenced Series')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

# Import required libraries
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
from google.colab import files
import statsmodels.api as sm
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller, kpss
from statsmodels.tsa.arima.model import ARIMA
from statsmodels.tsa.vector_ar.vecm import coint_johansen
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Upload Excel files
print("Please upload COST Excel file")
cost_upload = files.upload()
cost_filename = list(cost_upload.keys())[0]
cost_df = pd.read_excel(cost_filename)

print("Please upload HD Excel file")
hd_upload = files.upload()
hd_filename = list(hd_upload.keys())[0]
hd_df = pd.read_excel(hd_filename)

# Print available columns with better formatting
print("\nCOST DataFrame columns:")
for col in cost_df.columns:
    print(f"- '{col}'")
print("\nHD DataFrame columns:")
for col in hd_df.columns:
    print(f"- '{col}'")

# Ask user for the correct column name with guidance
print("\nNote: Enter the exact column name from above, including any spaces or case sensitivity")
close_column = input("Please enter the column name containing closing prices: ").strip()

# Verify the column exists in both DataFrames
if close_column not in cost_df.columns or close_column not in hd_df.columns:
    print(f"Error: Column '{close_column}' not found in one or both DataFrames")
    print("Available columns in COST:", list(cost_df.columns))
    print("Available columns in HD:", list(hd_df.columns))
    raise KeyError(f"Column '{close_column}' not found")

# Extract closing prices and clean the data
try:
    cost_close = cost_df[close_column].dropna()  # Remove NaN values
    hd_close = hd_df[close_column].dropna()  # Remove NaN values
except KeyError as e:
    print(f"Unexpected error accessing column '{close_column}': {e}")
    raise

# Check for infinite values and remove them
cost_close = cost_close[np.isfinite(cost_close)]
hd_close = hd_close[np.isfinite(hd_close)]

# Ensure both series have the same length
min_length = min(len(cost_close), len(hd_close))
cost_close = cost_close[:min_length]
hd_close = hd_close[:min_length]

# Check if data is empty after cleaning
if len(cost_close) == 0 or len(hd_close) == 0:
    raise ValueError("One or both series are empty after removing NaNs and infinite values. Please check your data.")

# Function for unit root tests
def unit_root_tests(series, name):
    print(f"\nUnit Root Tests for {name}:")

    # ADF Test
    adf_result = adfuller(series)
    print("ADF Test:")
    print(f'ADF Statistic: {adf_result[0]:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {adf_result[1]:.4f}')
    print(f'Critical Values: {adf_result[4]}')

    # KPSS Test
    kpss_result = kpss(series)
    print("\nKPSS Test:")
    print(f'KPSS Statistic: {kpss_result[0]:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {kpss_result[1]:.4f}')
    print(f'Critical Values: {kpss_result[3]}')

# Perform unit root tests
unit_root_tests(cost_close, "COST")
unit_root_tests(hd_close, "HD")

# Difference the series if non-stationary
cost_diff = cost_close.diff().dropna()
hd_diff = hd_close.diff().dropna()

# Function to find best ARMA model (using ARIMA with d=0)
def find_best_arma(series, name, max_p=3, max_q=3):
    best_aic = float('inf')
    best_order = None

    for p in range(max_p + 1):
        for q in range(max_q + 1):
            try:
                model = ARIMA(series, order=(p, 0, q))
                results = model.fit()
                if results.aic < best_aic:
                    best_aic = results.aic
                    best_order = (p, 0, q)
            except:
                continue

    print(f"\nBest ARMA model for {name}:")
    print(f"Order: {best_order}")
    print(f"AIC: {best_aic:.2f}")

    best_model = ARIMA(series, order=best_order).fit()
    return best_model

# Fit ARMA models
cost_arma = find_best_arma(cost_diff, "COST")
hd_arma = find_best_arma(hd_diff, "HD")

# Cointegration test
def cointegration_test(df):
    result = coint_johansen(df, det_order=0, k_ar_diff=1)
    print("\nJohansen Cointegration Test:")
    print(f"Trace statistic: {result.lr1}")
    print(f"Critical values (90%, 95%, 99%): {result.cvt}")

    for i in range(len(result.lr1)):
        if result.lr1[i] > result.cvt[i, 1]:  # 95% critical value
            print(f"r = {i}: Cointegration exists at 95% confidence level")
        else:
            print(f"r = {i}: No cointegration at 95% confidence level")

# Prepare data for cointegration
coint_df = pd.DataFrame({
    'COST': cost_close,
    'HD': hd_close
}).dropna()

# Run cointegration test
cointegration_test(coint_df)

# Plot the series
plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
plt.plot(cost_close, label='COST')
plt.plot(hd_close, label='HD')
plt.title('COST vs HD Closing Prices')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

# Plot the differenced series
plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
plt.plot(cost_diff, label='COST Diff')
plt.plot(hd_diff, label='HD Diff')
plt.title('Differenced Series')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

COST VS GOOG

In[6]:
# Import required libraries
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
from google.colab import files
import statsmodels.api as sm
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller, kpss
from statsmodels.tsa.arima.model import ARIMA
from statsmodels.tsa.vector_ar.vecm import coint_johansen
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Upload Excel files
print("Please upload COST Excel file")
cost_upload = files.upload()
cost_filename = list(cost_upload.keys())[0]
cost_df = pd.read_excel(cost_filename)

print("Please upload GOOG Excel file")
goog_upload = files.upload()
goog_filename = list(goog_upload.keys())[0]
goog_df = pd.read_excel(goog_filename)

# Print available columns with better formatting
print("\nCOST DataFrame columns:")
for col in cost_df.columns:
    print(f"- '{col}'")
print("\nGOOG DataFrame columns:")
for col in goog_df.columns:
    print(f"- '{col}'")

# Ask user for the correct column name with guidance
print("\nNote: Enter the exact column name from above, including any spaces or case sensitivity")
close_column = input("Please enter the column name containing closing prices: ").strip()

# Verify the column exists in both DataFrames
if close_column not in cost_df.columns or close_column not in goog_df.columns:
    print(f"Error: Column '{close_column}' not found in one or both DataFrames")
    print("Available columns in COST:", list(cost_df.columns))
    print("Available columns in GOOG:", list(goog_df.columns))
    raise KeyError(f"Column '{close_column}' not found")

# Extract closing prices and clean the data
try:
    cost_close = cost_df[close_column].dropna()  # Remove NaN values
    goog_close = goog_df[close_column].dropna()  # Remove NaN values
except KeyError as e:
    print(f"Unexpected error accessing column '{close_column}': {e}")
    raise

# Check for infinite values and remove them
cost_close = cost_close[np.isfinite(cost_close)]
goog_close = goog_close[np.isfinite(goog_close)]

# Ensure both series have the same length
min_length = min(len(cost_close), len(goog_close))
cost_close = cost_close[:min_length]
goog_close = goog_close[:min_length]

# Check if data is empty after cleaning
if len(cost_close) == 0 or len(goog_close) == 0:
    raise ValueError("One or both series are empty after removing NaNs and infinite values. Please check your data.")

# Function for unit root tests
def unit_root_tests(series, name):
    print(f"\nUnit Root Tests for {name}:")

    # ADF Test
    adf_result = adfuller(series)
    print("ADF Test:")
    print(f'ADF Statistic: {adf_result[0]:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {adf_result[1]:.4f}')
    print(f'Critical Values: {adf_result[4]}')

    # KPSS Test
    kpss_result = kpss(series)
    print("\nKPSS Test:")
    print(f'KPSS Statistic: {kpss_result[0]:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {kpss_result[1]:.4f}')
    print(f'Critical Values: {kpss_result[3]}')

# Perform unit root tests
unit_root_tests(cost_close, "COST")
unit_root_tests(goog_close, "GOOG")

# Difference the series if non-stationary
cost_diff = cost_close.diff().dropna()
goog_diff = goog_close.diff().dropna()

# Function to find best ARMA model (using ARIMA with d=0)
def find_best_arma(series, name, max_p=3, max_q=3):
    best_aic = float('inf')
    best_order = None

    for p in range(max_p + 1):
        for q in range(max_q + 1):
            try:
                model = ARIMA(series, order=(p, 0, q))
                results = model.fit()
                if results.aic < best_aic:
                    best_aic = results.aic
                    best_order = (p, 0, q)
            except:
                continue

    print(f"\nBest ARMA model for {name}:")
    print(f"Order: {best_order}")
    print(f"AIC: {best_aic:.2f}")

    best_model = ARIMA(series, order=best_order).fit()
    return best_model

# Fit ARMA models
cost_arma = find_best_arma(cost_diff, "COST")
goog_arma = find_best_arma(goog_diff, "GOOG")

# Cointegration test
def cointegration_test(df):
    result = coint_johansen(df, det_order=0, k_ar_diff=1)
    print("\nJohansen Cointegration Test:")
    print(f"Trace statistic: {result.lr1}")
    print(f"Critical values (90%, 95%, 99%): {result.cvt}")

    for i in range(len(result.lr1)):
        if result.lr1[i] > result.cvt[i, 1]:  # 95% critical value
            print(f"r = {i}: Cointegration exists at 95% confidence level")
        else:
            print(f"r = {i}: No cointegration at 95% confidence level")

# Prepare data for cointegration
coint_df = pd.DataFrame({
    'COST': cost_close,
    'GOOG': goog_close
}).dropna()

# Run cointegration test
cointegration_test(coint_df)

# Plot the series
plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
plt.plot(cost_close, label='COST')
plt.plot(goog_close, label='GOOG')
plt.title('COST vs GOOG Closing Prices')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

# Plot the differenced series
plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
plt.plot(cost_diff, label='COST Diff')
plt.plot(goog_diff, label='GOOG Diff')
plt.title('Differenced Series')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

# Import required libraries
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
from google.colab import files
import statsmodels.api as sm
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller, kpss
from statsmodels.tsa.arima.model import ARIMA
from statsmodels.tsa.vector_ar.vecm import coint_johansen
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Upload Excel files
print("Please upload TGT Excel file")
tgt_upload = files.upload()
tgt_filename = list(tgt_upload.keys())[0]
tgt_df = pd.read_excel(tgt_filename)

print("Please upload INTC Excel file")
intc_upload = files.upload()
intc_filename = list(intc_upload.keys())[0]
intc_df = pd.read_excel(intc_filename)

# Print available columns with better formatting
print("\nTGT DataFrame columns:")
for col in tgt_df.columns:
    print(f"- '{col}'")
print("\nINTC DataFrame columns:")
for col in intc_df.columns:
    print(f"- '{col}'")

# Ask user for the correct column name with guidance
print("\nNote: Enter the exact column name from above, including any spaces or case sensitivity")
close_column = input("Please enter the column name containing closing prices: ").strip()

# Verify the column exists in both DataFrames
if close_column not in tgt_df.columns or close_column not in intc_df.columns:
    print(f"Error: Column '{close_column}' not found in one or both DataFrames")
    print("Available columns in TGT:", list(tgt_df.columns))
    print("Available columns in INTC:", list(intc_df.columns))
    raise KeyError(f"Column '{close_column}' not found")

# Extract closing prices and clean the data
try:
    tgt_close = tgt_df[close_column].dropna()  # Remove NaN values
    intc_close = intc_df[close_column].dropna()  # Remove NaN values
except KeyError as e:
    print(f"Unexpected error accessing column '{close_column}': {e}")
    raise

# Check for infinite values and remove them
tgt_close = tgt_close[np.isfinite(tgt_close)]
intc_close = intc_close[np.isfinite(intc_close)]

# Ensure both series have the same length
min_length = min(len(tgt_close), len(intc_close))
tgt_close = tgt_close[:min_length]
intc_close = intc_close[:min_length]

# Check if data is empty after cleaning
if len(tgt_close) == 0 or len(intc_close) == 0:
    raise ValueError("One or both series are empty after removing NaNs and infinite values. Please check your data.")

# Function for unit root tests
def unit_root_tests(series, name):
    print(f"\nUnit Root Tests for {name}:")

    # ADF Test
    adf_result = adfuller(series)
    print("ADF Test:")
    print(f'ADF Statistic: {adf_result[0]:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {adf_result[1]:.4f}')
    print(f'Critical Values: {adf_result[4]}')

    # KPSS Test
    kpss_result = kpss(series)
    print("\nKPSS Test:")
    print(f'KPSS Statistic: {kpss_result[0]:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {kpss_result[1]:.4f}')
    print(f'Critical Values: {kpss_result[3]}')

# Perform unit root tests
unit_root_tests(tgt_close, "TGT")
unit_root_tests(intc_close, "INTC")

# Difference the series if non-stationary
tgt_diff = tgt_close.diff().dropna()
intc_diff = intc_close.diff().dropna()

# Function to find best ARMA model (using ARIMA with d=0)
def find_best_arma(series, name, max_p=3, max_q=3):
    best_aic = float('inf')
    best_order = None

    for p in range(max_p + 1):
        for q in range(max_q + 1):
            try:
                model = ARIMA(series, order=(p, 0, q))
                results = model.fit()
                if results.aic < best_aic:
                    best_aic = results.aic
                    best_order = (p, 0, q)
            except:
                continue

    print(f"\nBest ARMA model for {name}:")
    print(f"Order: {best_order}")
    print(f"AIC: {best_aic:.2f}")

    best_model = ARIMA(series, order=best_order).fit()
    return best_model

# Fit ARMA models
tgt_arma = find_best_arma(tgt_diff, "TGT")
intc_arma = find_best_arma(intc_diff, "INTC")

# Cointegration test
def cointegration_test(df):
    result = coint_johansen(df, det_order=0, k_ar_diff=1)
    print("\nJohansen Cointegration Test:")
    print(f"Trace statistic: {result.lr1}")
    print(f"Critical values (90%, 95%, 99%): {result.cvt}")

    for i in range(len(result.lr1)):
        if result.lr1[i] > result.cvt[i, 1]:  # 95% critical value
            print(f"r = {i}: Cointegration exists at 95% confidence level")
        else:
            print(f"r = {i}: No cointegration at 95% confidence level")

# Prepare data for cointegration
coint_df = pd.DataFrame({
    'TGT': tgt_close,
    'INTC': intc_close
}).dropna()

# Run cointegration test
cointegration_test(coint_df)

# Plot the series
plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
plt.plot(tgt_close, label='TGT')
plt.plot(intc_close, label='INTC')
plt.title('TGT vs INTC Closing Prices')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

# Plot the differenced series
plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
plt.plot(tgt_diff, label='TGT Diff')
plt.plot(intc_diff, label='INTC Diff')
plt.title('Differenced Series')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

In[8]:
# Import required libraries
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
from google.colab import files
import statsmodels.api as sm
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller, kpss
from statsmodels.tsa.arima.model import ARIMA
from statsmodels.tsa.vector_ar.vecm import coint_johansen
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Upload Excel files
print("Please upload TGT Excel file")
tgt_upload = files.upload()
tgt_filename = list(tgt_upload.keys())[0]
tgt_df = pd.read_excel(tgt_filename)

print("Please upload HD Excel file")
hd_upload = files.upload()
hd_filename = list(hd_upload.keys())[0]
hd_df = pd.read_excel(hd_filename)

# Print available columns with better formatting
print("\nTGT DataFrame columns:")
for col in tgt_df.columns:
    print(f"- '{col}'")
print("\nHD DataFrame columns:")
for col in hd_df.columns:
    print(f"- '{col}'")

# Ask user for the correct column name with guidance
print("\nNote: Enter the exact column name from above, including any spaces or case sensitivity")
close_column = input("Please enter the column name containing closing prices: ").strip()

# Verify the column exists in both DataFrames
if close_column not in tgt_df.columns or close_column not in hd_df.columns:
    print(f"Error: Column '{close_column}' not found in one or both DataFrames")
    print("Available columns in TGT:", list(tgt_df.columns))
    print("Available columns in HD:", list(hd_df.columns))
    raise KeyError(f"Column '{close_column}' not found")

# Extract closing prices and clean the data
try:
    tgt_close = tgt_df[close_column].dropna()  # Remove NaN values
    hd_close = hd_df[close_column].dropna()  # Remove NaN values
except KeyError as e:
    print(f"Unexpected error accessing column '{close_column}': {e}")
    raise

# Check for infinite values and remove them
tgt_close = tgt_close[np.isfinite(tgt_close)]
hd_close = hd_close[np.isfinite(hd_close)]

# Ensure both series have the same length
min_length = min(len(tgt_close), len(hd_close))
tgt_close = tgt_close[:min_length]
hd_close = hd_close[:min_length]

# Check if data is empty after cleaning
if len(tgt_close) == 0 or len(hd_close) == 0:
    raise ValueError("One or both series are empty after removing NaNs and infinite values. Please check your data.")

# Function for unit root tests
def unit_root_tests(series, name):
    print(f"\nUnit Root Tests for {name}:")

    # ADF Test
    adf_result = adfuller(series)
    print("ADF Test:")
    print(f'ADF Statistic: {adf_result[0]:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {adf_result[1]:.4f}')
    print(f'Critical Values: {adf_result[4]}')

    # KPSS Test
    kpss_result = kpss(series)
    print("\nKPSS Test:")
    print(f'KPSS Statistic: {kpss_result[0]:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {kpss_result[1]:.4f}')
    print(f'Critical Values: {kpss_result[3]}')

# Perform unit root tests
unit_root_tests(tgt_close, "TGT")
unit_root_tests(hd_close, "HD")

# Difference the series if non-stationary
tgt_diff = tgt_close.diff().dropna()
hd_diff = hd_close.diff().dropna()

# Function to find best ARMA model (using ARIMA with d=0)
def find_best_arma(series, name, max_p=3, max_q=3):
    best_aic = float('inf')
    best_order = None

    for p in range(max_p + 1):
        for q in range(max_q + 1):
            try:
                model = ARIMA(series, order=(p, 0, q))
                results = model.fit()
                if results.aic < best_aic:
                    best_aic = results.aic
                    best_order = (p, 0, q)
            except:
                continue

    print(f"\nBest ARMA model for {name}:")
    print(f"Order: {best_order}")
    print(f"AIC: {best_aic:.2f}")

    best_model = ARIMA(series, order=best_order).fit()
    return best_model

# Fit ARMA models
tgt_arma = find_best_arma(tgt_diff, "TGT")
hd_arma = find_best_arma(hd_diff, "HD")

# Cointegration test
def cointegration_test(df):
    result = coint_johansen(df, det_order=0, k_ar_diff=1)
    print("\nJohansen Cointegration Test:")
    print(f"Trace statistic: {result.lr1}")
    print(f"Critical values (90%, 95%, 99%): {result.cvt}")

    for i in range(len(result.lr1)):
        if result.lr1[i] > result.cvt[i, 1]:  # 95% critical value
            print(f"r = {i}: Cointegration exists at 95% confidence level")
        else:
            print(f"r = {i}: No cointegration at 95% confidence level")

# Prepare data for cointegration
coint_df = pd.DataFrame({
    'TGT': tgt_close,
    'HD': hd_close
}).dropna()

# Run cointegration test
cointegration_test(coint_df)

# Plot the series
plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
plt.plot(tgt_close, label='TGT')
plt.plot(hd_close, label='HD')
plt.title('TGT vs HD Closing Prices')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

# Plot the differenced series
plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
plt.plot(tgt_diff, label='TGT Diff')
plt.plot(hd_diff, label='HD Diff')
plt.title('Differenced Series')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

In[11]:
# Import required libraries
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
from google.colab import files
import statsmodels.api as sm
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller, kpss
from statsmodels.tsa.arima.model import ARIMA
from statsmodels.tsa.vector_ar.vecm import coint_johansen
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Upload Excel files
print("Please upload TGT Excel file")
tgt_upload = files.upload()
tgt_filename = list(tgt_upload.keys())[0]
tgt_df = pd.read_excel(tgt_filename)

print("Please upload GOOG Excel file")
goog_upload = files.upload()
goog_filename = list(goog_upload.keys())[0]
goog_df = pd.read_excel(goog_filename)

# Print available columns with better formatting
print("\nTGT DataFrame columns:")
for col in tgt_df.columns:
    print(f"- '{col}'")
print("\nGOOG DataFrame columns:")
for col in goog_df.columns:
    print(f"- '{col}'")

# Ask user for the correct column name with guidance
print("\nNote: Enter the exact column name from above, including any spaces or case sensitivity")
close_column = input("Please enter the column name containing closing prices: ").strip()

# Verify the column exists in both DataFrames
if close_column not in tgt_df.columns or close_column not in goog_df.columns:
    print(f"Error: Column '{close_column}' not found in one or both DataFrames")
    print("Available columns in TGT:", list(tgt_df.columns))
    print("Available columns in GOOG:", list(goog_df.columns))
    raise KeyError(f"Column '{close_column}' not found")

# Extract closing prices and clean the data
try:
    tgt_close = tgt_df[close_column].dropna()  # Remove NaN values
    goog_close = goog_df[close_column].dropna()  # Remove NaN values
except KeyError as e:
    print(f"Unexpected error accessing column '{close_column}': {e}")
    raise

# Check for infinite values and remove them
tgt_close = tgt_close[np.isfinite(tgt_close)]
goog_close = goog_close[np.isfinite(goog_close)]

# Ensure both series have the same length
min_length = min(len(tgt_close), len(goog_close))
tgt_close = tgt_close[:min_length]
goog_close = goog_close[:min_length]

# Check if data is empty after cleaning
if len(tgt_close) == 0 or len(goog_close) == 0:
    raise ValueError("One or both series are empty after removing NaNs and infinite values. Please check your data.")

# Function for unit root tests
def unit_root_tests(series, name):
    print(f"\nUnit Root Tests for {name}:")

    # ADF Test
    adf_result = adfuller(series)
    print("ADF Test:")
    print(f'ADF Statistic: {adf_result[0]:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {adf_result[1]:.4f}')
    print(f'Critical Values: {adf_result[4]}')

    # KPSS Test
    kpss_result = kpss(series)
    print("\nKPSS Test:")
    print(f'KPSS Statistic: {kpss_result[0]:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {kpss_result[1]:.4f}')
    print(f'Critical Values: {kpss_result[3]}')

# Perform unit root tests
unit_root_tests(tgt_close, "TGT")
unit_root_tests(goog_close, "GOOG")

# Difference the series if non-stationary
tgt_diff = tgt_close.diff().dropna()
goog_diff = goog_close.diff().dropna()

# Function to find best ARMA model (using ARIMA with d=0)
def find_best_arma(series, name, max_p=3, max_q=3):
    best_aic = float('inf')
    best_order = None

    for p in range(max_p + 1):
        for q in range(max_q + 1):
            try:
                model = ARIMA(series, order=(p, 0, q))
                results = model.fit()
                if results.aic < best_aic:
                    best_aic = results.aic
                    best_order = (p, 0, q)
            except:
                continue

    print(f"\nBest ARMA model for {name}:")
    print(f"Order: {best_order}")
    print(f"AIC: {best_aic:.2f}")

    best_model = ARIMA(series, order=best_order).fit()
    return best_model

# Fit ARMA models
tgt_arma = find_best_arma(tgt_diff, "TGT")
goog_arma = find_best_arma(goog_diff, "GOOG")

# Cointegration test
def cointegration_test(df):
    result = coint_johansen(df, det_order=0, k_ar_diff=1)
    print("\nJohansen Cointegration Test:")
    print(f"Trace statistic: {result.lr1}")
    print(f"Critical values (90%, 95%, 99%): {result.cvt}")

    for i in range(len(result.lr1)):
        if result.lr1[i] > result.cvt[i, 1]:  # 95% critical value
            print(f"r = {i}: Cointegration exists at 95% confidence level")
        else:
            print(f"r = {i}: No cointegration at 95% confidence level")

# Prepare data for cointegration
coint_df = pd.DataFrame({
    'TGT': tgt_close,
    'GOOG': goog_close
}).dropna()

# Run cointegration test
cointegration_test(coint_df)

# Plot the series
plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
plt.plot(tgt_close, label='TGT')
plt.plot(goog_close, label='GOOG')
plt.title('TGT vs GOOG Closing Prices')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

# Plot the differenced series
plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
plt.plot(tgt_diff, label='TGT Diff')
plt.plot(goog_diff, label='GOOG Diff')
plt.title('Differenced Series')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

In[12]:
# Import required libraries
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
from google.colab import files
import statsmodels.api as sm
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller, kpss
from statsmodels.tsa.arima.model import ARIMA
from statsmodels.tsa.vector_ar.vecm import coint_johansen
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Upload Excel files
print("Please upload INTC Excel file")
intc_upload = files.upload()
intc_filename = list(intc_upload.keys())[0]
intc_df = pd.read_excel(intc_filename)

print("Please upload HD Excel file")
hd_upload = files.upload()
hd_filename = list(hd_upload.keys())[0]
hd_df = pd.read_excel(hd_filename)

# Print available columns with better formatting
print("\nINTC DataFrame columns:")
for col in intc_df.columns:
    print(f"- '{col}'")
print("\nHD DataFrame columns:")
for col in hd_df.columns:
    print(f"- '{col}'")

# Ask user for the correct column name with guidance
print("\nNote: Enter the exact column name from above, including any spaces or case sensitivity")
close_column = input("Please enter the column name containing closing prices: ").strip()

# Verify the column exists in both DataFrames
if close_column not in intc_df.columns or close_column not in hd_df.columns:
    print(f"Error: Column '{close_column}' not found in one or both DataFrames")
    print("Available columns in INTC:", list(intc_df.columns))
    print("Available columns in HD:", list(hd_df.columns))
    raise KeyError(f"Column '{close_column}' not found")

# Extract closing prices and clean the data
try:
    intc_close = intc_df[close_column].dropna()  # Remove NaN values
    hd_close = hd_df[close_column].dropna()  # Remove NaN values
except KeyError as e:
    print(f"Unexpected error accessing column '{close_column}': {e}")
    raise

# Check for infinite values and remove them
intc_close = intc_close[np.isfinite(intc_close)]
hd_close = hd_close[np.isfinite(hd_close)]

# Ensure both series have the same length
min_length = min(len(intc_close), len(hd_close))
intc_close = intc_close[:min_length]
hd_close = hd_close[:min_length]

# Check if data is empty after cleaning
if len(intc_close) == 0 or len(hd_close) == 0:
    raise ValueError("One or both series are empty after removing NaNs and infinite values. Please check your data.")

# Function for unit root tests
def unit_root_tests(series, name):
    print(f"\nUnit Root Tests for {name}:")

    # ADF Test
    adf_result = adfuller(series)
    print("ADF Test:")
    print(f'ADF Statistic: {adf_result[0]:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {adf_result[1]:.4f}')
    print(f'Critical Values: {adf_result[4]}')

    # KPSS Test
    kpss_result = kpss(series)
    print("\nKPSS Test:")
    print(f'KPSS Statistic: {kpss_result[0]:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {kpss_result[1]:.4f}')
    print(f'Critical Values: {kpss_result[3]}')

# Perform unit root tests
unit_root_tests(intc_close, "INTC")
unit_root_tests(hd_close, "HD")

# Difference the series if non-stationary
intc_diff = intc_close.diff().dropna()
hd_diff = hd_close.diff().dropna()

# Function to find best ARMA model (using ARIMA with d=0)
def find_best_arma(series, name, max_p=3, max_q=3):
    best_aic = float('inf')
    best_order = None

    for p in range(max_p + 1):
        for q in range(max_q + 1):
            try:
                model = ARIMA(series, order=(p, 0, q))
                results = model.fit()
                if results.aic < best_aic:
                    best_aic = results.aic
                    best_order = (p, 0, q)
            except:
                continue

    print(f"\nBest ARMA model for {name}:")
    print(f"Order: {best_order}")
    print(f"AIC: {best_aic:.2f}")

    best_model = ARIMA(series, order=best_order).fit()
    return best_model

# Fit ARMA models
intc_arma = find_best_arma(intc_diff, "INTC")
hd_arma = find_best_arma(hd_diff, "HD")

# Cointegration test
def cointegration_test(df):
    result = coint_johansen(df, det_order=0, k_ar_diff=1)
    print("\nJohansen Cointegration Test:")
    print(f"Trace statistic: {result.lr1}")
    print(f"Critical values (90%, 95%, 99%): {result.cvt}")

    for i in range(len(result.lr1)):
        if result.lr1[i] > result.cvt[i, 1]:  # 95% critical value
            print(f"r = {i}: Cointegration exists at 95% confidence level")
        else:
            print(f"r = {i}: No cointegration at 95% confidence level")

# Prepare data for cointegration
coint_df = pd.DataFrame({
    'INTC': intc_close,
    'HD': hd_close
}).dropna()

# Run cointegration test
cointegration_test(coint_df)

# Plot the series
plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
plt.plot(intc_close, label='INTC')
plt.plot(hd_close, label='HD')
plt.title('INTC vs HD Closing Prices')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

# Plot the differenced series
plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
plt.plot(intc_diff, label='INTC Diff')
plt.plot(hd_diff, label='HD Diff')
plt.title('Differenced Series')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

INTC VS GOOG

In[13]:
# Import required libraries
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
from google.colab import files
import statsmodels.api as sm
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller, kpss
from statsmodels.tsa.arima.model import ARIMA
from statsmodels.tsa.vector_ar.vecm import coint_johansen
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Upload Excel files
print("Please upload INTC Excel file")
intc_upload = files.upload()
intc_filename = list(intc_upload.keys())[0]
intc_df = pd.read_excel(intc_filename)

print("Please upload GOOG Excel file")
goog_upload = files.upload()
goog_filename = list(goog_upload.keys())[0]
goog_df = pd.read_excel(goog_filename)

# Print available columns with better formatting
print("\nINTC DataFrame columns:")
for col in intc_df.columns:
    print(f"- '{col}'")
print("\nGOOG DataFrame columns:")
for col in goog_df.columns:
    print(f"- '{col}'")

# Ask user for the correct column name with guidance
print("\nNote: Enter the exact column name from above, including any spaces or case sensitivity")
close_column = input("Please enter the column name containing closing prices: ").strip()

# Verify the column exists in both DataFrames
if close_column not in intc_df.columns or close_column not in goog_df.columns:
    print(f"Error: Column '{close_column}' not found in one or both DataFrames")
    print("Available columns in INTC:", list(intc_df.columns))
    print("Available columns in GOOG:", list(goog_df.columns))
    raise KeyError(f"Column '{close_column}' not found")

# Extract closing prices and clean the data
try:
    intc_close = intc_df[close_column].dropna()  # Remove NaN values
    goog_close = goog_df[close_column].dropna()  # Remove NaN values
except KeyError as e:
    print(f"Unexpected error accessing column '{close_column}': {e}")
    raise

# Check for infinite values and remove them
intc_close = intc_close[np.isfinite(intc_close)]
goog_close = goog_close[np.isfinite(goog_close)]

# Ensure both series have the same length
min_length = min(len(intc_close), len(goog_close))
intc_close = intc_close[:min_length]
goog_close = goog_close[:min_length]

# Check if data is empty after cleaning
if len(intc_close) == 0 or len(goog_close) == 0:
    raise ValueError("One or both series are empty after removing NaNs and infinite values. Please check your data.")

# Function for unit root tests
def unit_root_tests(series, name):
    print(f"\nUnit Root Tests for {name}:")

    # ADF Test
    adf_result = adfuller(series)
    print("ADF Test:")
    print(f'ADF Statistic: {adf_result[0]:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {adf_result[1]:.4f}')
    print(f'Critical Values: {adf_result[4]}')

    # KPSS Test
    kpss_result = kpss(series)
    print("\nKPSS Test:")
    print(f'KPSS Statistic: {kpss_result[0]:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {kpss_result[1]:.4f}')
    print(f'Critical Values: {kpss_result[3]}')

# Perform unit root tests
unit_root_tests(intc_close, "INTC")
unit_root_tests(goog_close, "GOOG")

# Difference the series if non-stationary
intc_diff = intc_close.diff().dropna()
goog_diff = goog_close.diff().dropna()

# Function to find best ARMA model (using ARIMA with d=0)
def find_best_arma(series, name, max_p=3, max_q=3):
    best_aic = float('inf')
    best_order = None

    for p in range(max_p + 1):
        for q in range(max_q + 1):
            try:
                model = ARIMA(series, order=(p, 0, q))
                results = model.fit()
                if results.aic < best_aic:
                    best_aic = results.aic
                    best_order = (p, 0, q)
            except:
                continue

    print(f"\nBest ARMA model for {name}:")
    print(f"Order: {best_order}")
    print(f"AIC: {best_aic:.2f}")

    best_model = ARIMA(series, order=best_order).fit()
    return best_model

# Fit ARMA models
intc_arma = find_best_arma(intc_diff, "INTC")
goog_arma = find_best_arma(goog_diff, "GOOG")

# Cointegration test
def cointegration_test(df):
    result = coint_johansen(df, det_order=0, k_ar_diff=1)
    print("\nJohansen Cointegration Test:")
    print(f"Trace statistic: {result.lr1}")
    print(f"Critical values (90%, 95%, 99%): {result.cvt}")

    for i in range(len(result.lr1)):
        if result.lr1[i] > result.cvt[i, 1]:  # 95% critical value
            print(f"r = {i}: Cointegration exists at 95% confidence level")
        else:
            print(f"r = {i}: No cointegration at 95% confidence level")

# Prepare data for cointegration
coint_df = pd.DataFrame({
    'INTC': intc_close,
    'GOOG': goog_close
}).dropna()

# Run cointegration test
cointegration_test(coint_df)

# Plot the series
plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
plt.plot(intc_close, label='INTC')
plt.plot(goog_close, label='GOOG')
plt.title('INTC vs GOOG Closing Prices')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

# Plot the differenced series
plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
plt.plot(intc_diff, label='INTC Diff')
plt.plot(goog_diff, label='GOOG Diff')
plt.title('Differenced Series')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

# Import required libraries
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
from google.colab import files
import statsmodels.api as sm
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller, kpss
from statsmodels.tsa.arima.model import ARIMA
from statsmodels.tsa.vector_ar.vecm import coint_johansen
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Upload Excel files
print("Please upload HD Excel file")
hd_upload = files.upload()
hd_filename = list(hd_upload.keys())[0]
hd_df = pd.read_excel(hd_filename)

print("Please upload GOOG Excel file")
goog_upload = files.upload()
goog_filename = list(goog_upload.keys())[0]
goog_df = pd.read_excel(goog_filename)

# Print available columns with better formatting
print("\nHD DataFrame columns:")
for col in hd_df.columns:
    print(f"- '{col}'")
print("\nGOOG DataFrame columns:")
for col in goog_df.columns:
    print(f"- '{col}'")

# Ask user for the correct column name with guidance
print("\nNote: Enter the exact column name from above, including any spaces or case sensitivity")
close_column = input("Please enter the column name containing closing prices: ").strip()

# Verify the column exists in both DataFrames
if close_column not in hd_df.columns or close_column not in goog_df.columns:
    print(f"Error: Column '{close_column}' not found in one or both DataFrames")
    print("Available columns in HD:", list(hd_df.columns))
    print("Available columns in GOOG:", list(goog_df.columns))
    raise KeyError(f"Column '{close_column}' not found")

# Extract closing prices and clean the data
try:
    hd_close = hd_df[close_column].dropna()  # Remove NaN values
    goog_close = goog_df[close_column].dropna()  # Remove NaN values
except KeyError as e:
    print(f"Unexpected error accessing column '{close_column}': {e}")
    raise

# Check for infinite values and remove them
hd_close = hd_close[np.isfinite(hd_close)]
goog_close = goog_close[np.isfinite(goog_close)]

# Ensure both series have the same length
min_length = min(len(hd_close), len(goog_close))
hd_close = hd_close[:min_length]
goog_close = goog_close[:min_length]

# Check if data is empty after cleaning
if len(hd_close) == 0 or len(goog_close) == 0:
    raise ValueError("One or both series are empty after removing NaNs and infinite values. Please check your data.")

# Function for unit root tests
def unit_root_tests(series, name):
    print(f"\nUnit Root Tests for {name}:")

    # ADF Test
    adf_result = adfuller(series)
    print("ADF Test:")
    print(f'ADF Statistic: {adf_result[0]:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {adf_result[1]:.4f}')
    print(f'Critical Values: {adf_result[4]}')

    # KPSS Test
    kpss_result = kpss(series)
    print("\nKPSS Test:")
    print(f'KPSS Statistic: {kpss_result[0]:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {kpss_result[1]:.4f}')
    print(f'Critical Values: {kpss_result[3]}')

# Perform unit root tests
unit_root_tests(hd_close, "HD")
unit_root_tests(goog_close, "GOOG")

# Difference the series if non-stationary
hd_diff = hd_close.diff().dropna()
goog_diff = goog_close.diff().dropna()

# Function to find best ARMA model (using ARIMA with d=0)
def find_best_arma(series, name, max_p=3, max_q=3):
    best_aic = float('inf')
    best_order = None

    for p in range(max_p + 1):
        for q in range(max_q + 1):
            try:
                model = ARIMA(series, order=(p, 0, q))
                results = model.fit()
                if results.aic < best_aic:
                    best_aic = results.aic
                    best_order = (p, 0, q)
            except:
                continue

    print(f"\nBest ARMA model for {name}:")
    print(f"Order: {best_order}")
    print(f"AIC: {best_aic:.2f}")

    best_model = ARIMA(series, order=best_order).fit()
    return best_model

# Fit ARMA models
hd_arma = find_best_arma(hd_diff, "HD")
goog_arma = find_best_arma(goog_diff, "GOOG")

# Cointegration test
def cointegration_test(df):
    result = coint_johansen(df, det_order=0, k_ar_diff=1)
    print("\nJohansen Cointegration Test:")
    print(f"Trace statistic: {result.lr1}")
    print(f"Critical values (90%, 95%, 99%): {result.cvt}")

    for i in range(len(result.lr1)):
        if result.lr1[i] > result.cvt[i, 1]:  # 95% critical value
            print(f"r = {i}: Cointegration exists at 95% confidence level")
        else:
            print(f"r = {i}: No cointegration at 95% confidence level")

# Prepare data for cointegration
coint_df = pd.DataFrame({
    'HD': hd_close,
    'GOOG': goog_close
}).dropna()

# Run cointegration test
cointegration_test(coint_df)

# Plot the series
plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
plt.plot(hd_close, label='HD')
plt.plot(goog_close, label='GOOG')
plt.title('HD vs GOOG Closing Prices')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

# Plot the differenced series
plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
plt.plot(hd_diff, label='HD Diff')
plt.plot(goog_diff, label='GOOG Diff')
plt.title('Differenced Series')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

#@title Convert ipynb to HTML in Colab
# Upload ipynb
from google.colab import files
f = files.upload()

# Convert ipynb to html
import subprocess
file0 = list(f.keys())[0]
_ = subprocess.run(["pip", "install", "nbconvert"])
_ = subprocess.run(["jupyter", "nbconvert", file0, "--to", "html"])

# download the html
files.download(file0[:-5]+"html")
